medial to the cephalic vein. Both vessels are major superficial veins that facilitate venous drainage of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the anatomical relationships of other structures:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eulnar artery\u003C/strong\u003E travels in the anterior compartment of the forearm and is not anatomically related to the cephalic vein\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial nerve\u003C/strong\u003E descends in the posterior compartment of the arm before entering the anterior compartment\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebrachial artery\u003C/strong\u003E lies deep within the anterior compartment accompanied by venae comitantes\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emedian nerve\u003C/strong\u003E descends through the central portion of the anterior compartment\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese deeper neurovascular structures are separated from the superficial veins by the deep fascia of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The cephalic vein is a superficial vein located in the upper limb.","The cephalic vein runs along the lateral aspect of the arm and forearm.","The basilic vein is found inferior and medial to the cephalic vein in the arm."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67095"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18119"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67095","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67095"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-26T22:01:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-26T22:03:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10833"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81818"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4926"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiovascular","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23: